1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,688
Put this principle to work next time you must do something you don't want to do.

2
00:00:04,959 --> 00:00:09,009
Put this principle to work next time you find yourself becoming bored.

3
00:00:09,120 --> 00:00:12,529
Just dig in deeper and you dig up interest.

4
00:00:13,599 --> 00:00:14,769
2.

5
00:00:15,199 --> 00:00:17,808
In everything you do, life it up.

6
00:00:18,079 --> 00:00:23,168
Enthusiasm, or lack of it, shows through in everything you do and say.

7
00:00:23,439 --> 00:00:25,250
Life up your handshaking.

8
00:00:25,360 --> 00:00:27,490
When you shake hands, shake.

9
00:00:27,679 --> 00:00:31,168
Make your hand clasp say, I'm glad to know you.

10
00:00:31,279 --> 00:00:33,490
I am glad to see you again.

11
00:00:33,759 --> 00:00:38,209
A conservative mouse-like handshake is worse than no handshake at all.

12
00:00:38,319 --> 00:00:41,969
It makes people think, this guy is more dead than alive.

13
00:00:42,319 --> 00:00:46,928
Try to find a highly successful person with a conservative handshake.

14
00:00:47,039 --> 00:00:49,808
You'll have to look a long, long time.

15
00:00:51,039 --> 00:00:52,769
Life up your smiles.

16
00:00:52,959 --> 00:00:54,529
Smile with your eyes.

17
00:00:54,799 --> 00:00:58,769
Nobody likes an artificial, pasted-on, rubbery smile.

18
00:00:58,879 --> 00:01:00,928
When you smile, smile.

19
00:01:00,959 --> 00:01:02,289
Show a few teeth.

20
00:01:02,559 --> 00:01:06,448
Maybe your teeth aren't attractive, but that's really unimportant.

21
00:01:06,559 --> 00:01:09,808
For when you smile, people don't see your teeth.

22
00:01:09,919 --> 00:01:14,370
They see a warm, enthusiastic personality, someone they like.

23
00:01:15,199 --> 00:01:17,168
Life up your thank yous.

24
00:01:17,360 --> 00:01:22,289
A routine, automatic thank you is almost like saying, GLEEP GLEEP.

25
00:01:22,399 --> 00:01:23,889
It's just an expression.

26
00:01:23,919 --> 00:01:25,009
It says nothing.

27
00:01:25,199 --> 00:01:27,250
It doesn't accomplish results.

28
00:01:27,439 --> 00:01:31,089
Make your thank you mean thank you very much.

29
00:01:31,839 --> 00:01:33,490
Life up your talk!

30
00:01:33,839 --> 00:01:39,889
Dr. James F. Bender, the noted speech authority, in his excellent book, How to Talk Well,

31
00:01:39,919 --> 00:01:43,009
says, Is your good morning really good?

32
00:01:43,199 --> 00:01:46,048
Are your congratulations enthusiastic?

33
00:01:46,240 --> 00:01:49,168
Does your how are you sound interested?

34
00:01:49,439 --> 00:01:57,730
When you make a habit of coloring your words with sincere feelings, you'll notice a great uptake in your ability to hold attention.

35
00:01:58,559 --> 00:02:02,529
People go along with the fellow who believes what he says.

36
00:02:02,719 --> 00:02:04,048
Say it with life.

37
00:02:04,240 --> 00:02:06,849
Put vitality into your speaking.

38
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:14,289
Whether you are talking to a garden club, a prospect, or your children, put enthusiasm behind what you say.

39
00:02:14,639 --> 00:02:19,888
A sermon delivered enthusiastically may be remembered for months, even years.

40
00:02:20,078 --> 00:02:28,930
But a sermon delivered without enthusiasm will be mostly forgotten 167 hours before next Sunday rolls around.

41
00:02:29,920 --> 00:02:34,769
And when you put life in your talk, you automatically put more life in you.

42
00:02:34,960 --> 00:02:36,690
Just try this right now.

43
00:02:36,798 --> 00:02:40,848
Say out loud with force and vigor, I feel great today.

44
00:02:41,039 --> 00:02:45,170
Now, don't you actually feel better than you did before you said it?

45
00:02:45,279 --> 00:02:47,649
Make yourself alive all over.

46
00:02:48,078 --> 00:02:49,170
Life it up.

47
00:02:49,359 --> 00:02:54,289
Be sure everything you do and say tells people that fellow is alive.

48
00:02:54,399 --> 00:02:55,328
He means it.

49
00:02:55,440 --> 00:02:57,009
He's going places.

50
00:02:57,759 --> 00:02:59,009
3.

